org.kepler.provenance

Class ProvenanceRecorder

  • java.lang.Object
    • ptolemy.kernel.util.NamedObj
      • ptolemy.kernel.util.Attribute
        • org.kepler.provenance.ProvenanceRecorder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, SshEventListener, TagEventListener, WorkflowRenameListener, ActorFiringListener, ExecutionListener, Initializable, IOPortEventListener, Changeable, ChangeListener, Debuggable, DebugListener, Derivable, ModelErrorHandler, MoMLExportable, Moveable, Nameable, ValueListener

    public class ProvenanceRecorder
extends Attribute
implements ExecutionListener, ChangeListener, IOPortEventListener, ActorFiringListener, DebugListener, ValueListener, SshEventListener, Initializable, WorkflowRenameListener, TagEventListener
    A listener that records workflow provenance information. It implements several Kepler and Ptolemy listener interfaces in order to receive events for workflow specification, and execution. Provenance data is stored using a particular Recording implementation.
    Author:
    Daniel Crawl
    See Also:
    Recording

      • executionError

        public void executionError(Manager manager,
                           java.lang.Throwable throwable)
        Report an execution failure. This method will be called when an exception or error is caught by a manager. Exceptions are reported this way when the run() or startRun() methods of the manager are used to perform the execution. If instead the execute() method is used, then exceptions are not caught, and are instead just passed up to the caller of the execute() method. Those exceptions are not reported here (unless, of course, the caller of the execute() method does so).
        Specified by:
        executionError in interface ExecutionListener
        Parameters:
        manager - The manager controlling the execution.
        throwable - The throwable to report.

      • getDefaultProvenanceRecorder

        public static ProvenanceRecorder getDefaultProvenanceRecorder(NamedObj namedObj)
        Get the provenance recorder with for a NamedObj. The "default" provenance recorder for a NamedObj is stored at the top level of the hierarchy and is named using the TOP Recorder Name in the configuration file. If no default recorder exists, returns null.

      • getDefaultQueryable

        public static Queryable getDefaultQueryable(NamedObj namedObj)
                                     throws QueryException,
                                            RecordingException
        Get a queryable from the default provenance recorder for a NamedObj. The "default" provenance recorder for a NamedObj is stored at the top level of the hierarchy and is named using the TOP Recorder Name in the configuration file. If no default recorder exists, returns null. If the NamedObj is null, this returns the Queryable for the default provenance recording.
        Throws:
        QueryException
        RecordingException

      • addProvenanceRecorder

        public static boolean addProvenanceRecorder(CompositeActor container,
                                            ProvenanceEnabledListener listener,
                                            Effigy effigy)
                                     throws IllegalActionException,
                                            NameDuplicationException
        Add the default provenance recorder to a container if it does not already contain a provenance recorder.
        Parameters:
        container - The container in which to add the default provenance recorder.
        listener - Register this object to listen for provenance enabled events. This parameter can be null.
        effigy - The effigy displaying the container. This parameter can be null.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the default provenance recorder is recording. This may be false due to an unsupported director in container, or the default recording type set to ignore.
        Throws:
        IllegalActionException
        NameDuplicationException
